  "text": "The Android View rendering pipeline is orchestrated through a coordinated sequence of key components:\n\n1. **Choreographer.java** (core/java/android/view/Choreographer.java) - Receives VSYNC signals from the display (DisplayEventReceiver) and drives the frame scheduling. The scheduleFrameLocked() method schedules the doFrame() callback which executes all frame work including measure, layout, and draw phases synchronized to the display refresh rate.\n\n2. **ViewRootImpl.java** (core/java/android/view/ViewRootImpl.java) - The bridge between the WindowManager and the View hierarchy. The performTraversals() method is called from Choreographer's doFrame callback and orchestrates the complete measurement, layout, and draw phases. It calls performMeasure() to measure the entire view tree, performLayout() to position views, and performDraw() to render the views.\n\n3. **View.java** (core/java/android/view/View.java) - Defines the individual View class with three core methods: measure(widthMeasureSpec, heightMeasureSpec) which calculates view dimensions, layout(l, t, r, b) which positions the view on screen, and draw(canvas) which renders the view to a canvas. These methods are called recursively on the view hierarchy during ViewRootImpl's traversal phases.\n\n4. **RecordingCanvas.java** (graphics/java/android/graphics/RecordingCanvas.java) - A Canvas implementation that records drawing operations instead of immediately rendering them. Used during the View.draw() phase to capture all draw commands (drawRenderNode, drawPath, drawText, etc.) into a display list format for later GPU replay.\n\n5. **ThreadedRenderer.java** (core/java/android/view/ThreadedRenderer.java) - Extends HardwareRenderer and manages the rendering thread. The draw() method takes the recorded display list and passes it to the GPU rendering pipeline for hardware-accelerated rendering.\n\n6. **HardwareRenderer.java** (graphics/java/android/graphics/HardwareRenderer.java) - Provides the GPU-accelerated rendering bridge. Creates and maintains a shared render thread with GPU context. Contains drawRenderNode() to replay recorded drawing operations on the GPU and submit the final frame to the Surface for display.\n\nRendering Flow: Choreographer.doFrame() → ViewRootImpl.performTraversals() → (performMeasure() → View.measure(), performLayout() → View.layout(), performDraw() → View.draw() with RecordingCanvas) → ThreadedRenderer.draw() → HardwareRenderer.drawRenderNode() → GPU rendering and Surface submission."
}

